<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-03-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="212" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Wharton</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-03-21"><hi rend="italic">March 21,
                                1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 17th of
                            March, inclosing a letter from the Lake Carriers’ Association on the
                            subject of discriminating <pb facs="0362" n="274" xml:id="pg_274"/>
                            tolls in the Canadian canals, I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            transmitted a copy of your note and of its inclosure to the
                            governor-general of Canada.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>